{"title_page": "Matthew Alford", "text_new": "'''Matthew Alford''' is a British writer, performer and documentary producer.\n\n==Career==\nAlford's first book ''[[Reel Power: Hollywood Cinema and American Supremacy]]'' is based on his 2008 PhD thesis, which had applied [[Edward S. Herman]] and [[Noam Chomsky]]'s [[Propaganda Model]] to the film industry.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2019-05-09|title=Book review: Reel Power|url=https://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle-2-15039/book-review-reel-power-1-823740|website=www.scotsman.com}}</ref>\n\nHe has written articles for ''[[The Guardian]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/profile/matthewalford|title=Matthew Alford - The Guardian|website=The Guardian}}</ref> ''[[New Statesman]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/writers/316658|title=Writers|website=www.newstatesman.com}}</ref> and ''[[The Independent|Independent]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/author/matthew-alford|title=Matthew Alford|website=The Independent}}</ref> alternative media,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.creepyclassics.com/product.sc?productId=12571&categoryId=66|title=FILMFAX #124 - Magazine|website=www.creepyclassics.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ft.gjovaag.com/w/FT266|title=FT266 - FT Covers|website=ft.gjovaag.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ft.gjovaag.com/w/FT248|title=FT248 - FT Covers|website=ft.gjovaag.com}}</ref><ref>https://nexusmagazine.com/product/volume-27-number-1-downloadable/?v=79cba1185463</ref> and has appeared on [[RT (TV network)|RT]], Le Media and [[Al Jazeera]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.aljazeera.com/programmes/listeningpost/2017/10/covert-operations-cia-works-hollywood-171022101533765.html|title=Covert operations: How the CIA works with Hollywood|website=www.aljazeera.com}}</ref>  \nIn 2019, he worked with an unspecified newspaper on an article that highlighted omissions from mainstream coverage of Western foreign policy but it was dropped on the morning it was due to emerge.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://france.watsupeurope.com/news/les-auteurs-critiques-de-la-presse-mainstream-peinent-a-etre-publies/|title=Les auteurs critiques de la presse mainstream peinent \u00e0 \u00eatre publi\u00e9s &#124; WatsupEurope - Europe's Latest News & Entertainment Platform}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.peacenews.info/node/9433/how-western-media-support-state-terror-%E2%80%93-while-millions-die|title=How the Western media support state terror \u2013 while millions die &#124; Peace News|website=www.peacenews.info}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, Alford published a [[non-fiction novel]] ''[[The Writer with No Hands]],'' about producing a [[The Writer with No Hands|documentary]] on Hollywood screenwriter [[Gary DeVore|Gary Devore]]'s disappearance in 1997.<ref>https://www.vice.com/en_uk/article/gq95k9/the-writer-with-no-hands-gary-devore-matthew-alford Vice Magazine </ref> The film had premiered in the Future Cult Classics strand of the 2014 [[Hot Docs]] festival but was removed from circulation that year amidst concerns over bad taste, before being heavily re-edited for overseas television in 2018.<ref> www.projectionboothpodcast.com/2018/09/special-report-writer-with-no-hands-2017.html</ref>  Means TV distributed it worldwide in April 2020.<ref> http://www.relativeautonomy.com/blog/the-writer-with-no-hands</ref>\n\nIn September 2020, the [[Media Education Foundation]] is scheduled to distribute Theatres of Command, a documentary co-produced by Alford and based on a 2017 book National Security Cinema he co-authored about the role of the US military in re-writing film and TV.<ref>https://www.starandcrescent.org.uk/2020/04/20/the-feelgood-film-of-the-apocalypse-an-interview-with-derek-swannson/</ref><ref> https://www.wsws.org/en/articles/2020/02/27/nsec-f27.html</ref>  \n\nAlford played himself as a stand-up comedian in a short film Eagle Kill, released on 14th February 2020.<ref>https://www.starandcrescent.org.uk/2020/04/20/the-feelgood-film-of-the-apocalypse-an-interview-with-derek-swannson </ref>\n\n==Books==\n*''[[Reel Power:  Hollywood Cinema and American Supremacy]].'' London: [[Pluto Press]], 2010. {{ISBN|9780745329826}}.\n**2018. French language edition. With a new preface by Alford.\n*''The Writer with No Hands'' (2016).\n*''National Security Cinema: The Shocking New Evidence of Government Control in Hollywood'' ([[CreateSpace]], 2017). With Tom Secker.\n**2020.  Expanded French edition.\n*''Union Jackboot: What Your Media and Professors Don't Tell You About British Foreign Policy'' (CreateSpace, 2018). With T J Coles.\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.imdb.com/name/nm4038902/?ref_=tt_ov_st_sm IMDb Profile]\n*[https://researchportal.bath.ac.uk/en/persons/matthew-alford University of Bath Profile]\n* [https://www.opencomedy.com/matthewalford Open Comedy Profile]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Alford, Matthew}}\n[[Category:British male non-fiction writers]]\n[[Category:British investigative journalists]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:21st-century British male writers]]\n[[Category:British foreign policy writers]]\n[[Category:British film historians]]\n", "text_old": "'''Matthew Alford''' is a British writer, performer and documentary producer.\n\n==Career==\nAlford's first book ''[[Reel Power: Hollywood Cinema and American Supremacy]]'' is based on his 2008 PhD thesis, which had applied [[Edward S. Herman]] and [[Noam Chomsky]]'s [[Propaganda Model]] to the film industry.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=2019-05-09|title=Book review: Reel Power|url=https://www.scotsman.com/lifestyle-2-15039/book-review-reel-power-1-823740|website=www.scotsman.com}}</ref>\n\nHe has written articles for ''[[The Guardian]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/profile/matthewalford|title=Matthew Alford - The Guardian|website=The Guardian}}</ref> ''[[New Statesman]],''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.newstatesman.com/writer